page.title: 19WEST COKER AREA CLUBS
page.content: WEST COKER HAS A VILLAGE CLUB WHICH WAS STARTED IN 1922.THE LAND AND ORIGINAL HALL WAS SOLD TO THE VILLAGE FOR Â£700.MR. NATHAN THE OWNER OF THE MANOR AT THE TIME WAS THE FIRST PRESIDENT & THE "NATHAN CUP" IS STILL PLAYED FOR IN AN ANNUAL SKITTLES EVENT. THE CLUB WAS ORIGINALLY CALLED "THE LIBERTY NON POLITICAL CLUB" THE CLUB IS RUN BY A COMMITTEE OF VOLUNTEERS. IN 1985 A NEW CLUB WAS BUILD TO REPLACE THE ORIGINAL BUILDING. THIS NOW HAS AN EXCELLENT LARGE HALL,GAMES ROOM,SKITTLE ALLEY AND BAR. THE CLUB HAS A MEMBERSHIP OF ABOUT 200 PEOPLE.
